DESCRIPTION:The BrownConnect Careers in the Common Good (CCG) Winternships 
 Program\, offers students the opportunity to work on engaging projects for 
 social impact organizations and companies.\n\n\n  The projects last only tw
 o weeks but provide students with the opportunity to explore potential care
 er paths. Undergraduate students of all concentrations and class years are 
 welcome to apply.\n\n\n  This program will offer exclusively virtual intern
 ships in January 2023. Applications will be open through October 26th.  App
 lications for the program will open by October 7\, 2022.\n\n\n  If you have
  any questions about whether Winternships are right for you\, feel free to 
 attend our virtual information session or walk-in hours.\n\n\n  Info sessio
 n is: Oct. 18th\, 12pm | Virtual Walk-in hours: Oct. 21st & 25th\, 12-1pm |
  2nd floor Lobby • CareerLAB
LAST-MODIFIED:20221025T181658Z
LOCATION:Virtual Event
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Deadline: Careers in the Common Good Virtual Winternships (CCG Wint
 ernships)
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
