DESCRIPTION:Do you find public speaking intimidating or scary? Do you want 
 to more effectively communicate your ideas?\n\nAttend the Power of Public S
 peaking today\, Wednesday\, November 2 @ 4:30 PM! 85 Waterman Room 130.\n\n
 Professor Barbara Tannenbaum will be presenting a crash course on public sp
 eaking. These tips can be taken into every conversation anytime\, anywhere!
 \n\nProfessor Tannenbaum is a distinguished lecturer in the Theater and Per
 formance Studies department who teaches one of Brown’s hallmark courses: Pe
 rsuasive Communication.\n\nShe also consults with global business and profe
 ssional leaders on effective communication. She has advised senior politica
 l leaders including elected officials at the state and national level. In a
 ddition to global corporations\, her clientele includes the Council of Chie
 f Judges of the Appellate Courts of the United States\, The California Supr
 eme Court\, The Florida Supreme Court\, The International Monetary Fund\, M
 FA Boston\, The Museum of Modern Art\, and the Metropolitan Museum of Art.\
 n\nLight refreshments and snacks will be provided.\n\nYou won’t want to mis
 s this event!
LAST-MODIFIED:20221102T185151Z
LOCATION:85 Waterman Ave\, East Providence\, RI 02914\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:The Power of Public Speaking - A Presentation by Professor Barbara 
 Tannenbaum (Room 130)
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
